fields.title: Good For Studying/Working
fields.content:
I haven't had the food here. However, I dig how many vegan options they have.

It's a good place to study.  In fact, a number of key features found on VegPhilly were designed here!

fields.title: Tasty falafel
fields.content: This is a no-nonsense falafel joint that serves up tasty deep-fried food quick and fresh. Their falafel is some of the best in the city. You can also add hummus or babaganoush to your sandwich for a change of pace. Hummus and baba are just so-so. If falafel isn't your thing, they have excellent french fries.

fields.title: A great place to chill
fields.content: I go here when I want to get some reading done on the latest Semiotext(e) release. Friendly staff and great vibe. Decent sandwiches. Grindcore House has a good selection of loose-leaf teas from Premium Steap too.

On the fast/cheap/delectable matrix Chipotle strikes a great balance. 

However, this particular location has long lines of self-important college students and an overworked, weary staff serving burritos. You might be better off at another location.

fields.title: Blackbird Rocks!
fields.content: I'm always craving Blackbird pizza. They have great sandwiches too. I thought vegan wings were a silly idea until I tried theirs. Crispy, sweet, and satisfying. Now I can't decide what to order.

fields.title: Very impressed
fields.content: I went here with some friends and ordered the vegan chicken fingers. They were excellent. Just the right thickness and crispiness. The side salad had a delicious vinaigrette dressing. It seemed like all of the food had been prepared with care.

fields.title: Dare I say the best pizza in West Philly?
fields.content:
Dock Street serves great vegan pizza topped with mushrooms, sun-dried tomatoes, artichokes, and tofu. Get it well-done with a little black on the edges! They also brew their own beer.
  
The staff is sometimes spacey, but it's never too bad.

fields.title: Blackbird is dope
fields.content: Blackbird's got some crazy-good fake chicken wings! Sweet!

fields.title: Limited options, but excellent food
fields.content: Their salt and pepper tofu rocks! Lil' pricey, but tasty.

fields.title: this place is amazing!
fields.content: This place elevates vegetables to an art form. There's no fake steak and whatnot at this place. While you may see a dish with tofu or seitan, these are in the minority and the true standouts here are vegetables prepared meticulously. Desserts are also amazing. The house-made dairy free ice cream is incredible. I was advised to have the popcorn ice cream, but they were out, so I "made do" with maple. Really just can't say enough good things about Vedge.

fields.title: Tasty Lentils
fields.content: The injera is usually pretty fresh.  Abyssinia's Yemisir Wot is outstanding. Just the right amount of spice.

fields.title: Love Blackbird Pizza
fields.content: Great vegan food! I had no desire to try the vegan bbq wings, but once I did, I was hooked! Pizza is really good. Chickpea parm sandwich is great too.

fields.title: Collards are Killer!
fields.content: Whatever you order, make sure you get a side of collard greens-- they're amazing!

fields.title: This place is great!
fields.content: The chips and salsa that the Cantina serves as a complimentary appetizer are super delicious. The salsa verde is especially tasty! Their watermelon margaritas are also really nice.

fields.title: Super Spicy Food!
fields.content: Tamarind offers a spice scale from 1-7, where 7 may very well set you on fire. If you're after a pleasant spice, opt for a 2 or 3. If you really dig spicy foods, go for a 4. If you have an unusual tolerance for spice or numbed tastebuds, go for a 5. Anything beyond that, you're signing up for something ugly.

fields.title: Overall Really Good
fields.content: While the bahn mi is my favorite main, the wakame seaweed and soba noodle salad is my favorite starter. Both are satisfying and pretty healthy. If you're in a rush, though, this place isn't the best place to go, as it is usually packed and it can take some time to get your food. They do offer a large booze selection to hold you over while you wait, though.

fields.title: A lovely option for lunch or dinner.
fields.content: The original Adobe Cafe in Manayunk was always a favorite, so I was pleased to find a location in South Philadelphia when we moved here. The food is great, it never seems to be too crowded, and I vastly prefer the vegan and vegetarian options to the Cantina down the block. The atmosphere is very conducive to conversation, and the service has always been with a smile.

fields.title: Above Average Falafel
fields.content:
The falafel here really is fantastic. I do love to support Maoz for being all vegetarian and having a huge salad bar, but their falafel balls don't compare to Falafel Bar.

I've given them a 3 instead of 4 because the vegetables, especially the lettuce, leave something to be desired.

fields.title: Totally worth tracking down
fields.content: I get really excited thinking about how delicious Kung Fu Hoagies is. The two vegetarian owners plan to open a storefront at some point, but for now their location schedule changes weekly (the address above is where they sometimes set up on the UPenn campus). In addition to this location, they also do some days at Clark Park, and in South Philly at Passyunk and Dickinson. Find them!

fields.title: Golden Rings are unique!
fields.content:
The Golden Rings here are really interesting. Mashed potatoes wrapped in sheet tofu and fried. Comes out resembling a donut crossed with a dumpling. I wouldn't go to Su Xing without ordering these.

That said, I wouldn't eat an entire entree of Golden Rings because they are really heavy and they can get a little old. Split the Golden Rings with a friend and order something with greens in it too!
This quickly became one of our favorite after a run / work out spots to grab a bite to eat.   The wings ROCK and the probably have one of, if not the best crusts in the city.

fields.title: Outstanding!
fields.content: Amazing restaurant, if for some crazy reason you haven't been there...log off your computer and go now! I had their Seitan and lentil dish which was easily one of the most memorable plates of food I have ever eaten.  Their fingerling potatoes are outrageously good.  Service is top notch...wines, desserts - all outstanding.

fields.title: Superlative
fields.content: It's hard to overstate how much Landau and Jacoby have done to put Philly on the vegan map. Even setting aside the vegan chefs/entrepreneurs they've trained, Horizons woke up mainstream Philadelphians to the potential of vegan fine dining, and Vedge carries that even further. Note that reservations are needed for a table almost every night, but they serve the full menu at the bar, which has a nice atmosphere.

fields.title: YUM
fields.content: Blackbird Pizzeria...yum! This review might be a little aggressive because I've only been there once and tried one thing, but the Yukon pizza was so delicious. A little greasy, but not so much to ruin anything about the dish. The atmosphere does leave a little to be desired--it's very plain inside--but I got my order to go and it was ready promptly when I arrived. I will definitely be coming back here at some point to try something else!

fields.title: Hidden gem
fields.content: I love this place. It's on a pretty unassuming street corner, and it seems tiny from the outside, but there's a room with plenty of seating in the back. It's great to see a vegan place getting so much business. It's definitely a little punk/hardcore for me--the music can get loud--but once I threw on my headphones I didn't even care. I stayed for a while and got some work done, and while there had: the seitan sandwich, a buckeye, an almond butter cookie, a slice of zucchini bread, an early grey tea, and a hot chocolate. I have zero complaints about any of it- it was all delicious! Plus the staff were super friendly. Would recommend this to anyone, and will definitely be going back myself.

fields.title: Small menu, good food
fields.content: I do really like HipCityVeg. The staff are always incredibly friendly and the food is good. However, the atmosphere isn't great; it's a TINY location, and it's always packed with people. You should often be prepared to take your food to go as there will be no place to sit. Their menu is also a little small, but I haven't yet delved into all it has to offer. What I've had--the burger, the quinoa chili, the sweet potato fries, and noodle salad--have been good, so it definitely deserves a visit.

fields.title: Amazing.
fields.content: I love this place. Super friendly staff and always a good amount of options when it comes to their treats. Even my non-veg friends raved over their cookies when I brought them home! I will keep going back there all the time for the best vegan baked goods made right here in the city.

fields.title: Good food. Expensive and slow.
fields.content:
The place is nice and feels like you are eating at someone's house. It's cozy. The food was great and well prepared. 
The only drawbacks are the time it takes to eat there. Lunch is an hour and a half. Dinner is even longer.
It's not a bad thing, just keep this in mind when planning post-eating activities.

fields.title: Great Brunch
fields.content:
I have only eaten here for brunch but it was very good.  Unexpected pairings of tastes and textures.  I had the Yards beer battered seitan on belgian waffles with mustard greens underneath.
Nice atmosphere and good service.

fields.title: Awesome vegan food served quick!
fields.content: Granted they could use more space but that would not stop me from frequenting; yes, be prepared to not get a seat, may have to buy and fly.  The food is worth it though, best noodle salad I've ever had. Helpful staff.  More selection of desserts please!

The herbovore tofu tacos are amazing and have an Asian fusion twist. They even offer their own homemade vegan carrot cake which is served warm and topped with a melted cream cheese frosting. The cake is moist and loaded with walnuts. Plus Mad Mex has a decent selection of craft beers.

fields.title: Daiya cheese on "SuperVegan" pizza
fields.content: This is our (and probably most Manayunk vegans') go-to spot for takeout or delivered pizza on those nights when you say "you know what? Let's just have pizza." They use Daiya cheese on their vegan pizza. Crust is not Blackbird-quality but for something a few blocks away (vs. a trip all the way across Philadelphia) it's not bad!

fields.title: Best Vegan Ice Cream in Philly
fields.content: When you can find Kung Fu Hoagies and Little Baby's carts at the same event, you're set. You don't even have to worry--you'll have a belly full of awesome food. My favorite flavor is Thai Peanut, with Earl Grey Sriracha as a close second. I'm really curious about the Duck Sauce flavor...

fields.title: Vegan options clearly marked
fields.content:
I was pleasantly surprised that this place is a fast food Indian joint. It's nice to be able to get Indian food without the price and time commitment of table service. In fact, the prices here are AWESOME.

I give this place a lot of credit for how diligent they are about labeling vegan options. It is nice to see that there are two vegan options available daily, plus rice.

That said, the food was a little disappointing. I've had fast-food Indian that tasted a lot better than this. The lentils that are served daily left something to be desired.

Still, you'll probably find me there often because they offer Indian food without that "I'm probably eating ghee right now" feeling, are affordable, and there's nothing terrible about it. With the dismal competition in the area of Philadelphia Indian food, this is enough to earn my patronage.

fields.title: Love HCV
fields.content:
The Hip City Ranch Chicken style sandwich is my favorite thing to order here. I don't often have a need to try to mimic meat, but it's nice that this matches what I'm used to in a chicken sandwich so closely. My least favorite would be the steak. Too chunky for my taste the bread was really dry when I tried it, just not a fan. Yet after trying most of the menu, that was the one thing I disliked. Everything else was awesome. 

I don't know if I agree on the atmosphere comments. I believe HCV provides a great atmosphere they're just very successful and a small space doesn't help that. The lines always move quickly when I'm there and anytime I've wanted to stay and eat it's worked out (mind you I NEVER stay to eat during lunch hour on the weekdays) I think an additional location is in order due to this "problem" however:)

The smoked coconut club is so good, I'd eat it every day. I think the best part about it is the smoked coconut "bacon" which is delicious and also makes an appearance in one of their brunch options—the Vegan Rooster. After eating it, I tried to recreate it at home, but it's never as good.
The Tempeh Club is a great sandwich and it's awesome to have a veg option that isn't seitan or tofu. They usually have a vegan dessert as well. It can get loud and busy here even on weeknights.

So tofu scramble is the new default vegan breakfast/brunch item on omnivore menus which is AWESOME except many restaurants do not know how to properly prepare it. When I had it here, it was very oily. But thanks for trying, I guess. It was nice to be able to eat something besides fruit.

fields.title: Good Food
fields.content:
They've got some delicious vegan options, most of which center around vegan mayonaise.

I love this place because I've got some relatives who aren't interested in much besides American food and at the Royal Tavern, everyone can find something they like.

I've given a 3 for food instead of 4 because, like most bar food, everything is super salty. Maybe 3.5 would be more appropriate - the food truly is great.

fields.title: Good food for cheap
fields.content: Magic Carpet is one of the best food carts in Philadelphia. They consistently come up with interesting vegan specials and there's always good falafel and other Mediterranean dishes. The prices are very reasonable, but Magic Carpet has a bit of a following so be prepared to wait in line.

fields.title: Cafe of my dreams
fields.content: Grindcore House is probably the best cafe in Philadelphia. They have the largest selection of Vegan Treats (which are delivered on Thursdays), the sandwiches are fresh and unique from the typical vegan cheese steaks, and the staff are among the most pleasant people I've encountered in the coffee shop business. Do yourself a favor and become a regular here.

fields.title: My Favorite Lunch Spot
fields.content: Perfect place to go with friends on my lunch break. Food is ready quickly, and all the food is delicious. Pita, falafel, hummus, fries, fake chicken...it's all great.

fields.title: Yummy
fields.content: I've only had the "California Dreamin" so far, and it was awesome.  The veggie dog was cooked to perfection; the avocado and dressing on top was delicious. I'm definitely going to come back and try more varieties.

fields.title: Kitschy, but delicious
fields.suggested_feature_tags: Cash Only, Family Friendly (crayons and paper on table), Pet Friendly (has a dog that walks around),
fields.content: I was a little skeptical, but my food was awesome. I ordered the "Seitan Special" sandwich which was a Garlic Harissa Seitan hoagie with grilled peppers. It was really savory, delicious, dripping with garlicky oil. A little pricey, but worth it.

fields.title: Bubble Tea!
fields.content: I was so happy to find that Vegan Tree offers bubble tea, the only place I know of in Philly to get a vegan version! They offer two different options, milk tea and smoothie style, and a range of different flavors.  So far, I've tried the almond and coconut flavors in smoothie style; both offer just the right amount of sweetness and a good amount of tapioca!

fields.title: Nice Vibe
fields.content: The atmosphere of Adobe's Roxborough location carefully straddles Southwestern kitsch and authenticity. My entree, seitan sopes, was generously sized and super tasty. I had to take half of it home because I ate too much of the chips and salsa that came as a complimentary appetizer. If you're going by car, you may have to park a few blocks away because the restaurant is located in the middle of a residential neighborhood and it looks like parking is tough around there.

fields.title: Great vegan options
fields.content: What a great surprise. After reading a review from another reader, my family and I decided to give Mad Mex a try.  The first time wasn't successful as the line was long and we left. The second time was the charm -- and it was so worth it. The restaurant has tofu and mushrooms as an option in all of its tacos, enchiladas and burritos. It also has Daiya cheese and Tofutti sour cream. If you don't see what you want, you can create your own. We loved everything we got. Everything was so fresh and tasty. We will be back sooner rather than later.

fields.title: Awesome Lunch Specials
fields.content:
I routinely go here for the lunch specials and I always get the same thing: General Tso's Tofu, Brown Rice, Miso Soup, Spring Roll. The total price is $5.50, that's tough to beat.

The food is very savory and covered in brown goey goodness. The tofu is fried and crispy. Despite being called "Veggie Lovers", more than 75% of the meal is grains and proteins. Do not bring your yoga friends here.

It's a little cleaner than some of the other restaurants I've been to in Chinatown, the staff is friendly (if a little slow -- don't come in a hurry!) and the experience is consistent.

One word of warning - like many vegetarian asian restaurants, it is often unclear whether they are 100% vegan or nearly vegan. Veggie Lovers is definitely not 100% vegan. As of this writing, there are eggs in the fortune cookies.

fields.title: Shockingly good food
fields.content:
Miss Rachel makes amazing vegan food. I can honestly say that the salad I had at dinner was one of the best courses I've eaten anywhere. 

The atmosphere is very causal, but the service is attentive. Meat eaters will be happy here, as a lot of dishes have a "down-home" feeling.

Overall, a great experience and I can't wait to go back again!

fields.title: Mellow and Delicious
fields.content:
Ordered the vegan french toast today and it was awesome. Thick-cut "Texas" toast with crispy edges and rich, gooey centers thanks to its coconut-almond batter. Lightly crusted with some kind of crushed nut (I think), coated with powdered sugar, and served with a side of high-quality maple syrup. Nicely done!

I normally prefer to go straight to the Essene hot bar on weekends for french toast, but lately they've been skimping on providing condiments. I'm glad I can get something a little more thoughtfully prepared at POPE.

I rated the atmosphere as 3, but be warned, it is dark and dingy in here. It's calm, there's not usually brunch lines, and the staff is friendly. If you've got a hangover and want to enjoy food in peace, you're in for a treat. If you want to enjoy some sunshine, or get hyped on weekend brunch excitement, Sabrina's has you covered.

fields.title: Best sandwiches
fields.content: Recently tried The Steve, toasted BBQ tofu with tomato, arugula and aioli on ciabatta, and the Vegan Chicken Salad which is tempeh chicken salad on multigrain at GLC in Center City. The bread itself is BEAUTIFUL but overall the sandwiches are filling and really cheap. Will definitely be going there often now!

fields.title: Best snacks, coolest owner
fields.suggested_feature_tags: Family-friendly Atmosphere, Fun Atmosphere,Takeout Available, Smoothies/Juice Bar,
fields.content: Visited Mood Cafe with a friend for dessert. There are 25 flavors of lassi, which is a smoothie that is normally made with yogurt but can be made vegan with coconut, almond, or soy milk. I requested to have a combination of flavors and the owner was more than happy to try. He even gave us free samples and even made the Vegan Crazy Chaat on the house because I wasn't sure what it was. So sweet! The chaat was very fresh with delicious chutney and the service was wonderful.

This past weekend I finally took some time to hack on VegPhilly at Philly's only all-vegan coffee shop. I only wish I'd done so sooner. Grindcore House is charming. Good coffee, easy to get a table, the wifi is stable and there are tons of vegan snacks. 

Some of the same people were hanging around two days in a row, which, coupled with the friendliness of the staff, makes this place feel really comfortable. I like the music, but sometimes it was loud enough to feel like a music venue. Otherwise I'd give 4 stars for atmosphere.

The food is good enough for a coffee shop that doesn't have a kitchen. The Greenwich was light and delicious, perfect for "trying to concentrate and not get grease on my keyboard" eating.

Overall, Grindcore House is an awesome vegan business that's great for hanging around or trying to get some work done.

fields.title: Great Atmosphere and Healthy Food
fields.content:
I love the rustic feel of Pure Fare-- I'd give this atmosphere rating a 5/4 if I could. They've put a great deal of thought into the aesthetic of the cafe, as well as the usability of the website, and the menu items themselves.  

The food is colorful and healthy, and great for vegans who shy away from mock meats and other processed foods. I haven't had any of the entrees, but I have been really happy with the sandwiches and juices I've had.

I'm not sure if they're still doing this, but last summer, they were offering 1/2 price for the previous day's packaged sandwiches, which I thought was a damn fine deal.

fields.title: Better than the others
fields.content: For some reason, the ingredients at this Chipotle seem to taste fresher than at the other locations. Maybe it's the high turnover rate? Long lines at lunch are the norm. The space is also a little cramped with only a few tables and a lot of single seats.
Great to have a vegan option in Manayunk. Pizza is not half bad. They'll also make their salads without cheese if you request it.

Recently went here with a friend and had the winter melon soup, spring rolls, brown rice, and the crispy soy steak. I thought the soup was light and had a very pleasant flavor especially with the mushrooms!

However, the soy protein steak was just a crunchy thing in a thick drippy sauce. I would probably not get it again.

fields.title: Beautiful food, awesome space
fields.content: They have fresh and flavorful salads, smoothies, and soups with the ingredients listed on everything. There are many options and the space has a really cool atmosphere, but it's more expensive than other lunch places.

New Harmony is a wonderful option for lunch or dinner. Their prices are awesome, the wait staff is really nice, and the food is really great. I have it a 3/4 because it is not fancy gourmet dining but for vegan food it's amazing. The dim sum is a great value for 2 people or more and lets you get a really good feel for the place. They also have a pretty decent all you can eat buffet on Sunday evenings...well worth the trip! The restaurant itself is a little outdated and could us a new carpet/fresh coat of paint so it may not be the best place for a super fancy first date. However, it is cozy and clean. I would recommend this place 100 times over because of the wide selection, the tastiness of the food, and the ease of having a full vegan menu so you don't have to wonder what you can or can't eat.

I've eaten here a bunch of times, the food is always great. I particularly enjoy the sandwiches. Honestly, it's the best vegetarian lunch spot in Center City—it deserves more attention.

Staff is friendly, and helpful.

fields.title: healthy and delicious
fields.content: The menu is full of delicious, mostly (all?) organic and gluten-free mediterranean fixins to choose from as you build up your meal. I ordered a weekly special veggie burger not featured on the regular menu and it was delicious. This place does a great job with simple, high-quality food.
not bad

fields.name: Mi Lah Vegetarian
fields.notes: Offers diverse lunch, dinner, and brunch menus with creative combinations of vegetables, tofu, and seitan. There is plenty of seating so there's usually no wait for weekend brunch.

fields.name: Govinda's Gourmet To Go Vegetarian
fields.notes: Often a go-to-spot for vegan cheesesteaks, Govinda's offers a selection of mock meat sandwiches and wraps, in addition to housemade soups and salads. Govinda's To Go is the takeout/cafe style seating location, and Govinda's vegetarian is the dine-in restaurant next door, which is open Thursday-Sunday for dinner. Govinda's hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Maoz Vegetarian: Walnut Street
fields.notes: All vegetarian falafel takeout with a fully loaded self-serve topping/salad bar. Seating is limited. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Mama's Vegetarian
fields.notes: Offers hummus and pita sandwiches and veggie platters. Small seating area. Closed Saturdays.

fields.name: New Harmony Vegetarian Restaurant
fields.notes: Offers a range of mock chicken, beef, duck, and seafood entrees and dim sum options. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Blackbird Pizzeria
fields.notes: Philly's only all vegan pizzeria. You can opt for a 12" or an 18" pie, and rotating pies are sold by the slice. You can also get your hands on a seitan cheesesteak or a number of other hot sandwiches and wraps, in addition to wings, salads, soups, and Vegan Treats desserts.

fields.name: The Belgian Cafe
fields.notes: Offers stuffed tofu, vegan barbeque wings, seitan tacos, and a seitan vegan brunch option. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Vedge
fields.notes: Philly's premiere fine dining vegan restaurant, Vedge offers a tapas-style menu with an emphasis on locally sourced vegetables. Their Monday-Friday happy hour from 5-7pm features discounted food and drink specials. We recommend making a reservation, especially for groups larger than two.

fields.name: Singapore Kosher Vegetarian Restaurant - CLOSED
fields.notes: Offers a large vegan dim sum menu, in addition to mock meat dishes, tofu/vegetable plates, and chef's specials. This restaurant has not been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Sweet Freedom Bakery
fields.notes: One of Philly's fully vegan and gluten-free bakeries. Offers cupcakes, cookies, muffins, donuts, breads, and other sweet treats. Special orders accepted. Closed Mondays.

fields.name: Su Xing House
fields.notes: Offers a vast selection of tofu/vegetable plates and chef's specialties. Some plates have eggs but can be made without. Monday-Saturday lunch special includes a main, soup, and side for around $7. Closed Sundays.

fields.name: Kingdom of Vegetarians Restaurant
fields.notes: Offers a range of mock meats, tofu, and vegetable entrees. The Monday-Sunday lunch menu includes an entree with soup for $7. Note: no delivery. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: A Full Plate, Cafe & Catering - CLOSED
fields.notes: Offers a number of vegan dinner entrees and sides, including a mac and cheese made with three housemade nut cheeses. Vegan brunch options are tofu scramble and french toast. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Mugshots Coffeehouse & Cafe: Fairmount
fields.notes: Hit up Mugshots for a vegan hummus and veggie wrap, a tofu bahn mi, a mock meat bagel sandwich, or vegan chili. Also check out its events calendar for Open Mic Nights and other community events. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Grindcore House
fields.notes: Philadelphia's all-vegan coffee shop. Enjoy vegan sandwiches, sweet treats, coffee, and a distinctly punk/metal vibe.

fields.name: Royal Tavern
fields.notes: Vegan and vegetarian options are clearly noted on the menu, and there is usually at least one vegan special. Vegan entrees include a tofu and tempeh hash for brunch, and a tempeh club, vegan sloppy joe, and grilled sweet potato bahn mi for lunch and dinner.

fields.name: Sketch
fields.notes: Offers a vegan bean burger with several vegan sauce options, but no vegan cheese options. Also offers vegan special entrees, vegan desserts and milkshakes made with non-dairy ice cream.

fields.name: Essene Market & Cafe
fields.notes: An independently owned natural foods store featuring an all vegetarian, mostly vegan, hot bar/salad bar buffet with an emphasis on seasonal produce. Hot bar/salad bar is $8.99/lb, and there is a self-bussed cafe seating area. Essene hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Memphis Taproom
fields.notes: Vegan and vegetarian items are clearly marked on the menu, and there are sometimes vegan specials. Vegan options include hot sandwiches and a pumpkin pot pie on the lunch/dinner menu, and belgian waffles and tofu scramble on the brunch menu.

fields.name: San Samosa
fields.notes: Vegan items are not clearly marked on the menu, but vegetarian items are. Offers mock meat substitutes for curries, tikka masala, and vindaloo, in addition to vegetable biryani and korma dishes. This restaurant has not been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Black N Brew
fields.notes: Vegan brunch options include tofu scramble and breakfast burritos with no cheese or sour cream, and lunch options include hummus sandwiches and veggie burgers. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Charles Plaza
fields.notes: Offers a separate vegetarian menu with many vegan mock meat and tofu options. Monday-Friday lunch special includes soup and entree for $7. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Atiya Ola's Spirit First Foods
fields.notes: Unique cafe with vegan options and raw food options. Closed Tuesdays and Wednesdays. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: White Dog Cafe
fields.notes: While vegan and vegetarian items are clearly noted on the menu, there is only one vegan lunch/dinner main (stewed tofu and vegetables) and there are no vegan brunch options.

fields.name: Whole Foods Market: South Street
fields.notes: Deli counter includes a build-your-own $6 burrito/quesadilla/tacos station, and the large hot bar almost always has a number of vegan mains, sides, and soups. Salad bar includes a wide selection of raw food, grains, nuts, fruit, and marinated veg. $8.49/lb.

fields.name: Soy Cafe
fields.notes: Offers hot/cold sandwiches, wraps, and salads that can be made vegan. Also offers an extensive selection of freshly made smoothies and seasonal juices. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Hamifgash Restaurant
fields.notes: Offers falafel, hummus, and baba ghanoush sandwiches. Closed Saturdays. This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: Khyber Pass Pub
fields.notes: The Khyber is a Louisiana soul food joint that's a sister restaurant of the Royal Tavern and Cantina Dos Segundos + Los Caballitos. There are several vegan and vegetarian lunch/brunch/dinner entrees, and they are all clearly marked on the menu, There is also usually at least one vegan special.

fields.name: Veggie Lovers
fields.notes: Offers affordable Monday-Saturday lunch specials and an extensive dinner menu with traditional veggie and mock meat dishes. Lunch special includes a main, soup, and appetizer for around $6.

fields.name: Pure Sweets
fields.notes: Vegan, kosher, and gluten-free wholesale bakery that distributes at grocery stores and coffeeshops throughout the city. The address listed here is not a storefront; it's where Pure Sweets' commercial kitchen is located. Pure Sweets hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!

fields.name: South Philadelphia Tap Room

fields.name: Fino's Pizzeria & Restaurant

fields.name: Nile Cafe

fields.name: Qdoba Mexican Grill: West Philly

This restaurant hasn't been reviewed yet-- let us know what you think!
